    <specificfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p><strong>Worked solution</strong></p>
Let \(x\) be real number. Let's evaluate the sign of the difference of \(x + 1\) and \(x\).
We have: \(x + 1 - x = 1 > 0, \forall x \in \mathbb{R} \). So the quantification  \(  \forall x Q(x) \) is true.]]></text>
